The paper deals with decoding of error-correcting codes, specifically Reed-Solomon codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses various properties and bounds related to the decoding scheme, which could fall under the categories of data structures (cs.DS), distributed computing (cs.DC), coding theory (cs.CC), and signal processing (cs.SI).
